{| class="wikitable" |+ Comparison of Old and New Onsen Water Quality Labels<ref>{{Cite web|title=Reference Material: Comparison of Old and New Onsen Water Quality Labels |url=https://www.env.go.jp/nature/onsen/docs/senshitsumei26.pdf |format=PDF |publisher=Natural Environment Bureau, Ministry of the Environment |accessdate=2018-03-26 }} </ref> ! Old Label !! New Label !! Abbreviated Label |- | Sulfate Spring || Sulfate Spring || SO<sub>4</sub>-Spring |- | Pure Sulfate Spring || Sulfate Spring || SO<sub>4</sub>-Spring |- | Bitter Spring || Magnesium-Sulfate Spring || Mg-SO<sub>4</sub>-Spring |- | Glauber's Spring || Sodium-Sulfate Spring || Na-SO<sub>4</sub>-Spring |- | Gypsum Spring || Calcium-Sulfate Spring || Ca-SO<sub>4</sub>-Spring |- | Sodium-Chloride Sulfate Spring || Sodium-Sulfate-Chloride Spring || Na-SO<sub>4</sub>･Cl-Spring |- | Sodium-Calcium Sulfate Spring || Calcium-Sodium-Sulfate-Chloride Spring || Ca･Na-SO<sub>4</sub>･Cl-Spring |- | Magnesium-Sodium Sulfate Spring || Magnesium-Sodium-Sulfate-Chloride Spring || Mg･Na-SO<sub>4</sub>･Cl-Spring |}
== Definition == A sulfate spring is defined as a spring containing at least 1,000 mg of total dissolved substances per kilogram of water, with sulfate ions (SO<sub>4</sub><sup>2-</sup>) being the main anion.
== Health Benefits == ''Note: [[Health effects of hot springs|Effects]] are not guaranteed for all individuals.''
The following benefits are associated with sulfate springs:
=== Indications === ==== Bathing ==== * In addition to {{ill|General Indications|ja|一般的適応症|1=General Indications for hot spring use|12=draft|12=draft}}, these springs are said to help with: ** {{ill|Atherosclerosis|ja|Atherosclerosis|12=draft|12=draft}}
** Cuts and burns ** Chronic skin diseases
==== Drinking ==== * Chronic {{ill|Cholecystitis|ja|Cholecystitis|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Gallstone|ja|Gallstone|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Obesity|ja|Obesity|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Diabetes mellitus|ja|Diabetes mellitus|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Gout|ja|Gout|12=draft|12=draft}}
* Chronic {{ill|Constipation|ja|Constipation|12=draft|12=draft}}
=== Contraindications === * For bathing: {{ill|General Contraindications|ja|一般的適応症#一般的禁忌症|1=General_Indications_for_hot_spring_use#General_Contraindications|lt=General Contraindications for hot spring use|12=draft|12=draft}}
* For drinking: Not recommended during diarrhea. * For "Sodium-Sulfate Spring": Avoid drinking if you have {{ill|Kidney disease|ja|Kidney disease|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Hypertension|ja|Hypertension|12=draft|12=draft}} , {{ill|Edema|ja|Edema|12=draft|12=draft}} , or {{ill|Hyperthyroidism|ja|Hyperthyroidism|12=draft|12=draft}}in cases where the spring contains iodine. == Representative Onsen Areas == * {{ill|Atami Onsen|ja|熱海温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}(Shizuoka Prefecture)
* {{ill|Iizaka Onsen|ja|飯坂温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}(Fukushima Prefecture)
* {{ill|Tamatsukuri Onsen|ja|玉造温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}(Shimane Prefecture)
* {{ill|Minakami Onsen|ja|水上温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}(Gunma Prefecture) == Notes ==
