{{afc comment|1=This is questionable as I think it requires [[WP:MEDRS]] and I am surprised that jawiki has these claims not only not medically sourced but without medically reliable sources[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:10, 14 March 2025 (UTC)}}
[[File:140427 Chorakuen Tamatsukuri Onsen Matsue Shimane pref Japan15s3.jpg|thumb|right|Example of a sulfate spring ([[Tamatsukuri Onsen]])]] '''Sulfate Spring''' (硫酸塩泉, Ryūsan'en-sen) is a type of {{ill|Onsen|ja|温泉|1=Onsen|1=Onsen|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen|qq=}}<nowiki/>water quality classified under the {{ill|Medical Spring|ja|温泉#療養泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Medical Spring|qq=}} category of saline springs based on labeling. == Overview == Sulfate springs are named for their primary component, the sulfate salts of {{ill|Alkali metal|ja|Alkali metal|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Alkali metal|qq=}} s and {{ill|Alkaline earth metal|ja|Alkaline earth metal|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Alkaline earth metal|qq=}} s. These springs are popularly believed to have high medicinal benefits.
== Comparison of Old and New Labels == Below is a comparison of the old and new water quality labels for sulfate springs:
{| class="wikitable" |+ Comparison of Old and New Onsen Water Quality Labels<ref>{{Cite web|title=Reference Material: Comparison of Old and New Onsen Water Quality Labels |url=https://www.env.go.jp/nature/onsen/docs/senshitsumei26.pdf |format=PDF |publisher=Natural Environment Bureau, Ministry of the Environment |accessdate=2018-03-26 }} </ref> ! Old Label !! New Label !! Abbreviated Label |- | Sulfate Spring || Sulfate Spring || SO<sub>4</sub>-Spring |- | Pure Sulfate Spring || Sulfate Spring || SO<sub>4</sub>-Spring |- | Bitter Spring || Magnesium-Sulfate Spring || Mg-SO<sub>4</sub>-Spring |- | Glauber's Spring || Sodium-Sulfate Spring || Na-SO<sub>4</sub>-Spring |- | Gypsum Spring || Calcium-Sulfate Spring || Ca-SO<sub>4</sub>-Spring |- | Sodium-Chloride Sulfate Spring || Sodium-Sulfate-Chloride Spring || Na-SO<sub>4</sub>･Cl-Spring |- | Sodium-Calcium Sulfate Spring || Calcium-Sodium-Sulfate-Chloride Spring || Ca･Na-SO<sub>4</sub>･Cl-Spring |- | Magnesium-Sodium Sulfate Spring || Magnesium-Sodium-Sulfate-Chloride Spring || Mg･Na-SO<sub>4</sub>･Cl-Spring |}
== Definition == A sulfate spring is defined as a spring containing at least 1,000 mg of total dissolved substances per kilogram of water, with sulfate ions (SO<sub>4</sub><sup>2-</sup>) being the main anion.
== Health Benefits == ''Note: [[Health effects of hot springs|Effects]] are not guaranteed for all individuals.''
The following benefits are associated with sulfate springs:
=== Indications === ==== Bathing ==== * In addition to {{ill|General Indications|ja|一般的適応症|1=General Indications for hot spring use|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/General Indications|13=User:Immanuelle/General Indications for hot spring use|qq=}}, these springs are said to help with: ** {{ill|Atherosclerosis|ja|Atherosclerosis|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Atherosclerosis|qq=}}
** Cuts and burns ** Chronic skin diseases
==== Drinking ==== * Chronic {{ill|Cholecystitis|ja|Cholecystitis|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Cholecystitis|qq=}}
* {{ill|Gallstone|ja|Gallstone|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gallstone|qq=}}
* {{ill|Obesity|ja|Obesity|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Obesity|qq=}}
* {{ill|Diabetes mellitus|ja|Diabetes mellitus|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Diabetes mellitus|qq=}}
* {{ill|Gout|ja|Gout|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gout|qq=}}
* Chronic {{ill|Constipation|ja|Constipation|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Constipation|qq=}}
=== Contraindications === * For bathing: {{ill|General Contraindications|ja|一般的適応症#一般的禁忌症|1=General_Indications_for_hot_spring_use#General_Contraindications|lt=General Contraindications for hot spring use|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/General Contraindications|13=User:Immanuelle/General_Indications_for_hot_spring_use#General_Contraindications|qq=}}
* For drinking: Not recommended during diarrhea. * For "Sodium-Sulfate Spring": Avoid drinking if you have {{ill|Kidney disease|ja|Kidney disease|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kidney disease|qq=}}, {{ill|Hypertension|ja|Hypertension|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hypertension|qq=}} , {{ill|Edema|ja|Edema|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Edema|qq=}} , or {{ill|Hyperthyroidism|ja|Hyperthyroidism|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyperthyroidism|qq=}}in cases where the spring contains iodine. == Representative Onsen Areas == * {{ill|Atami Onsen|ja|熱海温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Atami Onsen|qq=}}(Shizuoka Prefecture)
* {{ill|Iizaka Onsen|ja|飯坂温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iizaka Onsen|qq=}}(Fukushima Prefecture)
* {{ill|Tamatsukuri Onsen|ja|玉造温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tamatsukuri Onsen|qq=}}(Shimane Prefecture)
* {{ill|Minakami Onsen|ja|水上温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minakami Onsen|qq=}}(Gunma Prefecture) == Notes ==
